</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f \colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> have a <fr:link
href="erct-000X.xml"
title="Quasi-inverse"
addr="erct-000X"
type="local">quasi-inverse</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> with incoherent counit <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon \colon  f\circ  g\sim  1_{B}]]></fr:tex> and unit <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta \colon  g\circ  f\sim  1_{A}]]></fr:tex>. We can <fr:em>correct</fr:em> the counit to obtain a coherent <fr:link
href="erct-000W.xml"
title="Inverse"
addr="erct-000W"
type="local">inverse</fr:link> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
