type="machine">unstable/796</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-796.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>The corrected counit <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon ' \colon  g\circ  f\sim  1_{A}]]></fr:tex> is defined like so:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[
  \epsilon ' x :\equiv 
  \epsilon 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f^{-1} x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
^{-1} \cdot  \mathsf {act}_{f}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \eta 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f^{-1} x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 \cdot  \epsilon  x
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>The coherence <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi \colon  \mathsf {act}_{f}\circ  \eta  \sim  \epsilon '\circ  f]]></fr:tex> can be constructed using our two naturality lemmas <fr:link
href="erct-001V.xml"
title="Naturality of homotopies"
addr="erct-001V"
type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number
addr="erct-001V" /></fr:link> and <fr:link
href="erct-001W.xml"
title="Naturality of homotopies onto the identity"
addr="erct-001W"
type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number
addr="erct-001W" /></fr:link>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
